New Records: Matt Olson is playing his 600th consecutive game, dating to 5/2/21. Only other streaks of 600+ to begin in divisional era (1969): 1982-98 Cal Ripken Jr: 2,632, 1975-83 Steve Garvey: 1,207, 2000-07 Miguel Tejada: 1,152, 1978-83 Pete Rose: 745, 1981-86 Dale Murphy: 740, 1973-78 Rose: 678, 1969-73 Sandy Alomar Sr: 661
Key Match Events: The Atlanta Braves suffered a tough loss on Saturday against the Toronto Blue Jays, falling 9-5.
